## UserService API Reference

The `UserService` class provides CRUD operations for user entities.

### Methods

| Method | Signature | Parameters | Return Type | Description |
|--------|-----------|------------|-------------|-------------|
| `getUserById` | `public User getUserById(String userId)` | `userId` (String) – Unique identifier for the user. | `User` | Retrieves a user by their unique ID. |
| `createUser` | `public void createUser(User user)` | `user` (User) – User object containing user details. | `void` | Persists a new user to the database. |
| `deleteUser` | `public boolean deleteUser(String userId)` | `userId` (String) – Unique identifier for the user. | `boolean` | Deletes the user; returns `true` if successful, `false` otherwise. |
| `listUsers` | `public List<User> listUsers(int page, int pageSize)` | `page` (int) – Page number for pagination.
`pageSize` (int) – Number of users per page. | `List<User>` | Returns a paginated list of users. |

### Example Usage
java
UserService userService = new UserService();

// Retrieve a user
User user = userService.getUserById("12345");

// Create a new user
User newUser = new User("john.doe", "John", "Doe");
userService.createUser(newUser);

// Delete a user
boolean deleted = userService.deleteUser("12345");

// List users (page 1, 20 users per page)
List<User> users = userService.listUsers(1, 20);


---

**Note:** All methods throw `UserNotFoundException` if the specified user ID does not exist.

